I didnt need my recent norwegian musical drifts to know the musical genius of Jan Garbarek. His aerial sounds have been a constant company through several years.
Soprano, tenor, bass saxophone, clarinet and flute are the instruments which he uses to paint his jazz landscapes with hues peculiar to him.
Sooner or later I would have to put together all his discography, and the time has come.

There are 78 albums: both from his main discography and from his collaborations.
All the album are zipped (since the number of files was too high for TPB).
The sampling rate is mostly 320kbps.
Different rates are signed in the name of the albums zips.

Enjoy :)
